</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[820,1437,1800,1882]" lastBlockId="11.[151,768,918,1393]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="10" pageNumber="107">
Jusqu’ici, la femelle restait inconnue; celle-ci est plus petite que le mâle; je donne donc la photographie, à l’échelle d’un mâle, d’un spécimen élevé au rang d’allotype (
<figureCitation box="[1289,1346,1858,1882]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[151,207,1021,1040]" captionTargetBox="[367,1227,222,969]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[265,1340,191,1021]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4 Pomponia linearis (Walker, 1850). Mâle (en haut) et femelle allotype (en dessous). (Photographies Michel Boulard)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3569912" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3569912/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="107">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, en bas). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,918,951]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">
<typeStatus box="[151,253,918,944]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Allotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[259,280,923,951]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">♀</specimenCount>
</emphasis>
(et 
<specimenCount box="[322,458,919,945]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">
2 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[342,458,919,945]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">paratypes</emphasis>
</specimenCount>
<specimenCount box="[464,505,923,951]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">♀♀</specimenCount>
) – 
<collectingCountry box="[540,659,918,944]" name="Thailand" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Thaïlande</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion country="Thailand" name="Chiang Mai" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Province de Chiang Maï</collectingRegion>
